gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Raptors 117, Bucks 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Toronto Raptors defeated the Milwaukee Bucks, 117-111. Gary Trent tied a season-high with 31 points, along with seven 3PM as RJ Barrett (26 points, seven rebounds) and Immanuel Quickley (25 points, 11 rebounds, nine assists) added 51 points. Damian Lillard (36 points, four 3PM, five rebounds, six assists) and Khris Middleton (21 points, five rebounds, six assists) led the Bucks in the loss.
